org.springframework.jms.support

接口 JmsHeaders


  • public interface JmsHeaders
    Pre-defined names and prefixes to be used for setting and/or retrieving JMS attributes from/to generic message headers.
    从以下版本开始:
    4.1
    作者:
    Mark Fisher, Stephane Nicoll

    • 字段概要

      字段 
      限定符和类型 字段和说明
      static java.lang.String CORRELATION_ID
      Correlation ID for the message.
      static java.lang.String DELIVERY_MODE
      Distribution mode.
      static java.lang.String DESTINATION
      Name of the destination (topic or queue) of the message.
      static java.lang.String EXPIRATION
      Message expiration date and time.
      static java.lang.String MESSAGE_ID
      Unique identifier for a message.
      static java.lang.String PREFIX
      Prefix used for JMS API related headers in order to distinguish from user-defined headers and other internal headers (e.g. correlationId).
      static java.lang.String PRIORITY
      The message priority level.
      static java.lang.String REDELIVERED
      Specify if the message was resent.
      static java.lang.String REPLY_TO
      Name of the destination (topic or queue) the message replies should be sent to.
      static java.lang.String TIMESTAMP
      Date and time of the message sending operation.
      static java.lang.String TYPE
      Message type label.

    • 字段详细资料

      • PREFIX

        static final java.lang.String PREFIX
        Prefix used for JMS API related headers in order to distinguish from user-defined headers and other internal headers (e.g. correlationId).
        另请参阅:
        SimpleJmsHeaderMapper, 常量字段值

      • CORRELATION_ID

        static final java.lang.String CORRELATION_ID
        Correlation ID for the message. This may be the MESSAGE_ID of the message that this message replies to. It may also be an application-specific identifier.
        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSCorrelationID(), 常量字段值

      • DESTINATION

        static final java.lang.String DESTINATION
        Name of the destination (topic or queue) of the message.

        Read-only value.

        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSDestination(), Destination, Queue, Topic, 常量字段值

      • DELIVERY_MODE

        static final java.lang.String DELIVERY_MODE
        Distribution mode.

        Read-only value.

        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSDeliveryMode(), DeliveryMode, 常量字段值

      • EXPIRATION

        static final java.lang.String EXPIRATION
        Message expiration date and time.

        Read-only value.

        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSExpiration(), 常量字段值

      • MESSAGE_ID

        static final java.lang.String MESSAGE_ID
        Unique identifier for a message.

        Read-only value.

        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSMessageID(), 常量字段值

      • PRIORITY

        static final java.lang.String PRIORITY
        The message priority level.

        Read-only value.

        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSPriority(), 常量字段值

      • REPLY_TO

        static final java.lang.String REPLY_TO
        Name of the destination (topic or queue) the message replies should be sent to.
        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSReplyTo(), 常量字段值

      • REDELIVERED

        static final java.lang.String REDELIVERED
        Specify if the message was resent. This occurs when a message consumer fails to acknowledge the message reception.

        Read-only value.

        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSRedelivered(), 常量字段值

      • TYPE

        static final java.lang.String TYPE
        Message type label. This type is a string value describing the message in a functional manner.
        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSType(), 常量字段值

      • TIMESTAMP

        static final java.lang.String TIMESTAMP
        Date and time of the message sending operation.

        Read-only value.

        另请参阅:
        Message.getJMSTimestamp(), 常量字段值
